Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 69
H.P. 33 House of Representatives, January 8, 2025
Paper and Single-use Bags
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant
to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative BAGSHAW of Windham.
Cosponsored by Senator LIBBY of Cumberland and
Representatives: COLLINS of Sidney, COOPER of Windham, JAVNER of Chester.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 38 MRSA ยง1611, as amended by PL 2021, c. 186, ยง18, is repealed.
3 SUMMARY
44 This bill repeals the law restricting the use of recycled paper bags, reusable bags made
55 of plastic and single-use carry-out bags.
